Title: Comprehensive System Integrity Repair, Windows Update Recovery, and Preventive OS Maintenance
Classification: Preventive Security Maintenance / System Integrity Validation
Execution Period: September 2025
Status: Completed Successfully
Executive Summary
This procedure was executed to restore full system integrity, repair Windows Update functionality, remove corrupted components, eliminate potential persistence vectors, and establish a clean, secure, and verified baseline. All steps were repeated until scans and repair tools returned no integrity violations.
Objectives
	• Restore Windows system integrity and clean baseline
	• Repair Windows Update functionality
	• Remove corrupted system components and residual files
	• Verify disk integrity, component store health, and update mechanisms
Core System Integrity & Repair Procedure
Step 1 — Disk Cleanup
	• Removed temporary files, Windows Update cache, delivery optimization files, and unnecessary system files
Step 2 — System File Integrity Check
	• Command: sfc /scannow → scanned all protected Windows files, replaced corrupted files
	• Repeated until no integrity violations
Step 3 — Full Disk Integrity Check
	• Command: chkdsk /r /f → repaired filesystem, detected bad sectors, recovered data
	• Restart required to complete
Step 4 — DISM Component Store Repair & Cleanup
	• Commands executed:
DISM /Online /Cleanup-Image /CheckHealth
DISM /Online /Cleanup-Image /ScanHealth
DISM /Online /Cleanup-Image /RestoreHealth
DISM /Online /Cleanup-Image /AnalyzeComponentStore
DISM /Online /Cleanup-Image /StartComponentCleanup
DISM /Online /Cleanup-Image /StartComponentCleanup /ResetBase
DISM /Online /Cleanup-Image /SPSuperseded
DISM /Cleanup-Mountpoints
sfc /scannow
	• Verified component store, repaired components, removed obsolete files; repeated until clean
Step 5 — TrustedInstaller Service Repair (If Required)
	• Fixed Windows Resource Protection service startup issues
	• Commands:
sc config trustedinstaller start=auto
net start trustedinstaller
sfc /scannow
Step 6 — Windows Update System Reset
	• Stopped update services, cleared update cache
	• Network reset:
ipconfig /renew 
	ipconfig /renew6 
	ipconfig /release 
	ipconfig /release6 
	ipconfig /flushdns
netsh winsock reset
	• Reset Windows Update Catalog
Step 7 — Windows Update Recovery via In-Place Upgrade
	• Media Creation Tool → latest ISO → “Keep personal files and apps”
	• Rebuilt core components while preserving data
Step 8 — Manual Windows Update Installation
	• Updates downloaded from Microsoft Update Catalog to bypass automated failures
Step 9 — Maintenance Software Toolchain
	• Tools used: system cleanup, driver/software management, registry and persistence inspection
	• Verified removal of orphaned files, unauthorized persistence mechanisms
Step 10 — Driver Update & System Stabilization
	• Restore Point created before updates
	• Drivers updated incrementally, stability validated, new Restore Point created after stable configuration
	• Temporary driver utilities removed
Step 11 — Network Stack & Connectivity Maintenance
	• Verified DNS settings and network integrity
Step 12 — Network Monitoring & Intrusion Detection
	• Tools: packet capture, outbound connection detection, traffic inspection, persistence verification
Step 13 — SSD Configuration & Integrity Verification
	• Verified SSD health and partition integrity; extended system partition as required
Step 14 — GPU & System Performance Maintenance
	• Cleared GPU cache; restored power plans to default settings
Step 15 — Power Management & Stability Optimization
	• Advanced power settings configured for thermal stability and improved reliability
Step 16 — Firmware & Thermal Control
	• Verified fan and thermal behavior with monitoring software
Step 17 — Preventive Maintenance Policy
	• Frequency: 2–3 times/year
	• Includes: restore point creation, driver verification, integrity scans, network monitoring, software cleanup, security validation
Final Outcome
	• Windows component store repaired
	• Windows Update restored
	• Disk and system integrity verified
	• No malware persistence detected
	• Network stack integrity validated
	• System returned to stable, secure baseline
	• All tools returned clean results
